Bungoma Governor Kenneth Lusaka has urged residents to invest in dairy farming. He said Bungoma has the potential to be a major milk supplier.Lusaka said they are setting up milk coolers. &ldquo;I will also support dairy cooperatives to access milk packaging machines, milk ATMs and homogenisers,&rdquo; he said.Lusaka spoke in Kimaeti when he launched the Bumula Dairy Farmers Cooperative Society. In March, the county government distributed hundreds of dairy cows to women&rsquo;s groups. &ldquo;I&rsquo;m glad that the progress and the impact of the project is being felt by the people,&rdquo; Lusaka said.